{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"body":"Update after reading origin/main HEAD (6845b8326) + measuring the store:\n\nWHAT'S ALREADY LANDED (not needed from us):\n- Fix #2 (skip archived tickets): DONE in 6845b8326 (_is_archived_ticket wired into _collect_all).\n- Batched introducing-commit map + position map (bug 1cc0 / disabled-absurd-iggypops):\n  build_introducing_commit_map (4262e3794) and build_position_commit_map are built once in cli().\n- Despite both, verify-identity STILL took 44.7 min on 6845b8326 (archived tickets are a\n  minority; the bulk of the 808 signed events are in ACTIVE tickets). The run's *failure* on\n  that sha is unrelated — the build-and-test cells failed fast; verify-identity itself passed.\n\nREMAINING / DECISION:\n- Fix #1 (gate the era-verify when require_authenticated is off): still needed. Safe — verified\n  the era result feeds only the enforced exit code + informational counts/JSON(tests only).\n- Fix #3 (--base windowing to enforce_since): the enforced window is currently 195 added event\n  files / 301 commits since the re-flip anchor (~1 day). It shrinks the scan now, BUT enforce_since\n  is NOT auto-advanced and the store grows ~300 commits/day, so the window (and runtime) creeps\n  back up. Windowing is a real but DECAYING mitigation.\n- Fix #4 (DURABLE, recommended): the per-event era-verify cost is\n  keys_valid_at_anchor -> _resolve = resolve_event_commit, a FULL-HISTORY `git log` per keyring\n  record per event (~1.25s of the 1.28s/event in cProfile). cli() already builds the batched\n  position/commit maps but does NOT thread them into verify_authorship_at_commit/keys_valid_at_anchor.\n  Wiring the batched map into that hot path makes each event O(1) git instead of O(keyring×history)\n  — behavior-preserving (same commit resolved, just via the map), and it fixes the whole-store cost\n  regardless of window size. This is the root-cause fix.\n\nPLAN for this ticket: implement Fix #1 + Fix #3 (as directed) with TDD + a held-out security-invariant\ntest (an unsigned event AFTER enforce_since must still FAIL the gate under windowed collection), and\nfile Fix #4 as the durable follow-up (or fold in if low-risk)."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784350346832568001,"uuid":"d2fc96c2-a65a-41d0-869d-b5a95456132d"}